    - target: {fileID: 11438438, guid: 298daca7decb9f846b5ff996ee97a495, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Text
      value: This shows you how to swipe between multiple different UI screens. This
        is done by using the <color=#0FF>LeanDrag</color>, <color=#0FF>LeanSnap</color>,
        and <color=#0FF>LeanConstrainAnchoredPosition</color> components on the parent
        GameObject. The <color=#0FF>LeanSnap.IntervalRect</color> setting is set
        to 1, so it snaps every page size, and <color=#0FF>LeanConstrainAnchoredPosition.RectMin
        & Max</color> is set to -2 & 0, so it can slide between page offset -2, -1,
        0.
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
